    "body": "> I would love for this sort of interaction to work! I think, however, that tailoring this aspect for all usage of panic for one use case in an IDE, however, may not be the best motivation for the change. For example a targeted way to modify panic messages for just the test runner would work well here.\n\nAgreed, having a way to have more control over what panic outputs sounds great to me. Maybe the best solution is in general improvements to the assert! family of macros.\n\nThanks!\n",
